      <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="Adver-FAQ">
        <ul class="sec2-FAQ-driver-ul">
          <li>
            <button class="accordion btn-filter">How much Exposure is one Spotted equals to&#63;</button>

            <div class="panel">
            <p>Each Spotted is equivalent to a baseline of 800 miles &#47; month and an average of 100&#44;000 impressions &#47; month. There is slight variability depending upon the size of the geography we are targeting.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <button class="accordion btn-filter">How do you calculate impressions&#63;</button>

            <div class="panel">
            <p>Spotted has partnered with a Traffic Engineering firm that calculates the impression count by overlaying the gps data collected daily from every car&#44; on top of traffic algorithms.
            Important variables that our model takes into consideration include the average daily traffic count on the roads&#44; the number of lanes, the average load per vehicle, and the time of day.
            The traffic volume is weighted in consideration with the amount of time the Spotted spent on that specific road. Impression counts are aggregated for each Spotted and collected daily.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <button class="accordion btn-filter">Who are these drivers and why did they join Spotted&#63;</button>

            <div class="panel">
            <p>Spotted drivers are safe high-mileage drivers in the community who want to make residual income for driving around with a brand on their car. It&#39;s passive side income for doing something they&#39;re already
            doing &#45; driving. More specifically our Spotted drivers are a collection of esteemed community members. They are a collection of nurses&#44; engineers&#44; teachers, etc.&#44; who have a consistent driving pattern&#44;
            are safe drivers, have a 2008 model car or newer&#44; and like and support the brand their driving with.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <button class="accordion btn-filter">How do you protect my brand&#39;s image&#63;</button>

            <div class="panel">
            <p>Spotted uses a strong deterrent &#45; if our Spotted drivers commit an act of reckless or aggressive driving&#44; not only do they get immediately removed from the campaign&#44; they also have to reimburse Spotted
            &#36;500.00 for the cost of the decal we put on their car. They registered with Spotted to make residual income from their commute &#45; not to give money away. They have a strong incentive to not drive carelessly.</p>
            <p>Additionally&#44; Spotted has created a process called EASI &#40;pronounced &#34;Easy&#34;&#41; that we use when setting up every campaign. It is an acronym that stands for educate&#44; align&#44; screen&#44; inform.</p>
            <br>
            <p><strong>EDUCATE</strong> &#45; We educate the surrounding community as to what the relationship is between the driver&#44; the brand on the car&#44; and Spotted. We do this by placing a small Spotted sticker on the back of every
            car along with a &#34;How&#39;s my driving&#34; decal. It&#39;s important for viewers to know that this is a Spotted carrying a brand on their car. This way the risk of brand reputation being impacted by a Spotted driver
            falls back on Spotted&#44; not our partnering brand.</p>
            <p><strong>ALIGN</strong> &#45; We align the brand with drivers who are a safe demographic. That means a lot of soccer moms and dads&#44; and not a lot of 18 &#45; 24 year olds.</p>
            <p><strong>SCREEN</strong> &#45; All drivers are background screened and driving record checked. There can be no major infractions committed on either.</p>
            <p><strong>INFORM</strong> &#45; After Spotted conducts our interview and screening process, we speak with every one of our car drivers emphasizing the importance of safe driving and representing a brand.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <button class="accordion btn-filter">What actions are taken if a Spotted driver cuts someone off or gets a complaint&#63;</button>

            <div class="panel">
            <p>The demographic of driver we select and their driving record decreases the chance of this happening. Inevitably however&#44; drivers are human so every so often this does occur &#40;sometimes justified&#44; sometimes not&#41;.
            The outlet for the driver to report the Spotted drivers&#39; driving behavior is through a uniquely ID&#39;d phone number on the back of their car. When a complaint is received Spotted notifies the client&#44;
            and uses our best judgment as to whether the complaint is legitimate &#40;we check the gps data to make sure stories align and also hear from the Spotted driver themselves&#41;. If an act of reckless driving was committed&#44;
            the car driver is immediately removed from the campaign and they have to pay Spotted &#36;300.00 for the cost of the wrap.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>

          <li>
            <button class="accordion btn-filter">What happens if Spotted driver get into an accident&#63;</button>

            <div class="panel">
            <p>If an accident occurs our drivers promptly notify Spotted which in turn get&#39;s passed back to the client. The decal is removed from the car and a replacement driver is used for the
            duration of the campaign. This is a rare occurrence as all of our drivers have been screened and vetted to ensure the highest degree of safe driving. </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <button class="accordion btn-filter">Legally speaking&#44; how does this affect the driver&#39;s insurance&#63;</button>

            <div class="panel">
            <p>The legal arrangement Spotted structures with its&#39; Spotted driver is that of an independent contractor. We contract the right to put our client&#39;s brand &#40;you&#41; on the side of their car.
            We explicitly state that the Spotted drivers are never to drive around for the sake of advertising &#45; this ensures that the Spotted driver personal auto&#45;liability coverage stays intact.
            If an accident occurs&#44; the Spotted driver personally held auto-liability coverage is in effect because they were driving for personal reasons&#59; not for commercial reasons.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <button class="accordion btn-filter">How do you select Spotted drivers for my campaign&#63;</button>

